cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with a robotics problem of inferring 3D shapes of unknown objects in clutter, which suggests that it belongs to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also utilizes computer vision techniques for observing the objects and their motions, which makes Computer Vision (cs.CV) a likely sub-category as well. The probabilistic framework and the use of a physics engine for verifying hypothesized geometries suggest that Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category. The paper also presents an efficient algorithm for inferring occluded parts of objects, which suggests that Machine Learning (cs.LG) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with geometric modeling and manipulation planning, which suggests that Graphics (cs.GR) is a possible sub-category as well.
